[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6698,
        "end_time": 8793,
        "text": "What makes a book a book?"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8793,
        "end_time": 12828,
        "text": "Is it just anything that stores\nand communicates information?"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 12828,
        "end_time": 14509,
        "text": "Or does it have to do with paper,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 14509,
        "end_time": 15236,
        "text": "binding,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 15236,
        "end_time": 15984,
        "text": "font,"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 15984,
        "end_time": 16736,
        "text": "ink,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 16736,
        "end_time": 17973,
        "text": "its weight in your hands,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 17973,
        "end_time": 19803,
        "text": "the smell of the pages?"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 19803,
        "end_time": 21112,
        "text": "Is this a book?"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 21112,
        "end_time": 22486,
        "text": "Probably not."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 22486,
        "end_time": 23483,
        "text": "But is this?"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 23483,
        "end_time": 24763,
        "text": "To answer these questions,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 24763,
        "end_time": 27525,
        "text": "we need to go back to the start\nof the book as we know it"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 27525,
        "end_time": 30698,
        "text": "and understand how these elements\ncame together to make something"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 30698,
        "end_time": 33240,
        "text": "more than the sum of their parts."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 33240,
        "end_time": 36859,
        "text": "The earliest object that we think of\nas a book is the codex,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 36859,
        "end_time": 39949,
        "text": "a stack of pages bound along one edge."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 39949,
        "end_time": 42395,
        "text": "But the real turning point in book history"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 42395,
        "end_time": 46575,
        "text": "was Johannes Gutenberg&#39;s\nprinting press in the mid-15th century."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 46575,
        "end_time": 51642,
        "text": "The concept of moveable type had been\ninvented much earlier in Eastern culture,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 51642,
        "end_time": 55833,
        "text": "but the introduction of Gutenberg&#39;s\npress had a profound effect."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 55833,
        "end_time": 59949,
        "text": "Suddenly, an elite class of monks\nand the ruling class"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 59949,
        "end_time": 62531,
        "text": "no longer controlled \nthe production of texts."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 62531,
        "end_time": 64328,
        "text": "Messages could spread more easily,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 64328,
        "end_time": 67333,
        "text": "and copies could constantly be produced,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 67333,
        "end_time": 70432,
        "text": "so printing houses popped up\nall over Europe."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 70432,
        "end_time": 75268,
        "text": "The product of this bibliographic boom\nis familiar to us in some respects,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 75268,
        "end_time": 77949,
        "text": "but markedly different in others."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 77949,
        "end_time": 82796,
        "text": "The skeleton of the book is paper,\ntype, and cover."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 82796,
        "end_time": 87044,
        "text": "More than 2000 years ago,\nChina invented paper as a writing surface,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 87044,
        "end_time": 90516,
        "text": "which was itself predated \nby Egyptian papyrus."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 90516,
        "end_time": 92707,
        "text": "However, until the 16th century,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 92707,
        "end_time": 95236,
        "text": "Europeans mainly wrote \non thin sheets of wood"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 95236,
        "end_time": 99176,
        "text": "and durable parchment\nmade of stretched animal skins."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 99176,
        "end_time": 103022,
        "text": "Eventually, the popularity of paper\nspread throughout Europe,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 103022,
        "end_time": 107673,
        "text": "replacing parchment for most printings\nbecause it was less expensive in bulk."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 107673,
        "end_time": 111576,
        "text": "Inks had been made by combining\norganic plant and animal dyes"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 111576,
        "end_time": 113046,
        "text": "with water or wine,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 113046,
        "end_time": 115519,
        "text": "but since water doesn&#39;t stick\nto metal type,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 115519,
        "end_time": 120144,
        "text": "use of the printing press required\na change to oil-based ink."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 120144,
        "end_time": 123513,
        "text": "Printers used black ink made of\na mixture of lamp soot,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 123513,
        "end_time": 124395,
        "text": "turpentine,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 124395,
        "end_time": 126138,
        "text": "and walnut oil."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 126138,
        "end_time": 128236,
        "text": "And what about font size and type?"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 128236,
        "end_time": 132577,
        "text": "The earliest movable type pieces\nconsisted of reversed letters"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 132577,
        "end_time": 136673,
        "text": "cast in relief on the ends of\nlead alloy stocks."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 136673,
        "end_time": 139147,
        "text": "They were handmade and expensive,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 139147,
        "end_time": 142865,
        "text": "and the designs were as different\nas the people who carved their molds."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 142865,
        "end_time": 147151,
        "text": "Standardization was not really possible\nuntil mass manufacturing"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 147151,
        "end_time": 150830,
        "text": "and the creation of an accessible\nword processing system."
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 150830,
        "end_time": 156230,
        "text": "As for style, we can thank Nicolas Jenson\nfor developing two types of Roman font"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 156230,
        "end_time": 158610,
        "text": "that led to thousands of others,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 158610,
        "end_time": 161248,
        "text": "including the familiar Times Roman."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 161248,
        "end_time": 164013,
        "text": "Something had to hold all this together,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 164013,
        "end_time": 166399,
        "text": "and until the late 15th century,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 166399,
        "end_time": 168732,
        "text": "covers consisted of either wood,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 168732,
        "end_time": 171045,
        "text": "or sheets of paper pasted together."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 171045,
        "end_time": 174698,
        "text": "These would eventually be replaced\nby rope fiber millboard,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 174698,
        "end_time": 179482,
        "text": "originally intended for high quality\nbindings in the late 17th century,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 179482,
        "end_time": 182947,
        "text": "but later as a less expensive option."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 182947,
        "end_time": 186550,
        "text": "And while today&#39;s mass produced\ncover illustrations are marketing tools,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 186550,
        "end_time": 190304,
        "text": "the cover designs of early books \nwere made to order."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 190304,
        "end_time": 192839,
        "text": "Even spines have a history."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 192839,
        "end_time": 196406,
        "text": "Initially, they were not considered\naesthetically important,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 196406,
        "end_time": 199743,
        "text": "and the earliest ones were flat,\nrather than rounded."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 199743,
        "end_time": 202516,
        "text": "The flat form made the books\neasier to read"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 202516,
        "end_time": 205522,
        "text": "by allowing the book to rest easily\non a table."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 205522,
        "end_time": 210453,
        "text": "But those spines were damaged\neasily from the stresses of normal use."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 210453,
        "end_time": 212580,
        "text": "A rounded form solved that issue,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 212580,
        "end_time": 214555,
        "text": "although new problems arose,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 214555,
        "end_time": 217389,
        "text": "like having the book close in\non itself."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 217389,
        "end_time": 219263,
        "text": "But flexibility was more important,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 219263,
        "end_time": 221609,
        "text": "especially for the on-the-go reader."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 221609,
        "end_time": 225266,
        "text": "As the book evolves\nand we replace bound texts"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 225266,
        "end_time": 227855,
        "text": "with flat screens and electronic ink,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 227855,
        "end_time": 230953,
        "text": "are these objects and files really books?"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 230953,
        "end_time": 232436,
        "text": "Does the feel of the cover"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 232436,
        "end_time": 235738,
        "text": "or the smell of the paper add something\ncrucial to the experience?"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 235738,
        "end_time": 238837,
        "text": "Or does the magic live only within\nthe words,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 238837,
        "end_time": 241018,
        "text": "no matter what their presentation?"
    }
]